
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `funzip` baraye baz kardane file-haye zip shode estefade mishavad.  In dastoor be shoma ejazeh mideh ta file-haye zip ra dar hale ke file asli zip shode dast nakhorde mimanad, baz konid va estefade konid.  Be ebarate digar, `funzip` file-haye zip shode ra dar directory-e movaghat baz mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `funzip -l filename.zip` --> 📜 Liste file-haye dakhele file zip ra neshon midahad, bedune baz kardan.
    🔹 `funzip -p password filename.zip` --> 🔑 Agar file zip shode password dashte bashad, ba in dastoor mitavanid an ra baz konid.
    🔹 `funzip -q filename.zip` --> 🤫  Dar hale baz kardan, hich payami chap nakon. (Quiet mode)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ funzip file.zip

    🔹 File `file.zip` ra baz mikonad va file-haye dakhelash ra dar directory-e movaghat gharar midahad.

    $ funzip -l file.zip

    🔹 Listi az file-haye dakhele `file.zip` ra chap mikonad bedune baz kardan.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ funzip archive.zip && cd /tmp/funzip_*

    🔹 `archive.zip` ra baz mikonad va shoma ra be pooshe-ye movaghati ke file-ha dar anja baz shodeand, rahnamayi mikonad. Shoma mitavanid az file-ha estefade konid va bad az tamam shodan kar, pooshe-ye movaghati ra pak konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `funzip` command is used to extract files from a zip archive. It allows you to access the contents of a zip file without actually extracting the archive permanently. Essentially, `funzip` extracts the zip file into a temporary directory.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `funzip -l filename.zip` --> 📜 Lists the files contained within the zip archive without extracting them.
    🔹 `funzip -p password filename.zip` --> 🔑 If the zip archive is password-protected, this allows you to extract it using the given password.
    🔹 `funzip -q filename.zip` --> 🤫 Suppresses all output messages during extraction. (Quiet mode)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ funzip file.zip

    🔹 Extracts `file.zip` and places the contents in a temporary directory.

    $ funzip -l file.zip

    🔹 Prints a list of the files contained within `file.zip` without extracting it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ funzip archive.zip && cd /tmp/funzip_*

    🔹 Extracts `archive.zip` and then navigates you to the temporary directory where the extracted files are located. You can work with the files and delete the temporary directory when you are finished.
